Archived on 2025-10-05, this archive contains 693 messages between 10:37:29 PM to 2:55:33 AM.
					It has 19 dice rolls.

messages.content: Reverberations - Session 3
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: May 06, 2008. About noon. Tom's Pool & Bar.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're done with the booking procedure of Jane Margolis. You took the time off to get some lunch at an old-timer bar near the courthouse. The radio is playing some song from the generation preceeding yours.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Looks pretty lively this time of the day.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You're having a tuna melt sandwich with fries and diet coke. It reminds you of Miami.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The dry heat on the other hand is a sharp contrast. The moist tropical breeze of Dade is an unending summer vacation year-round. Here, it's scorching, blazing hot in the desert.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Likewise with the environment. Miami is always a pleasure to be in, full of colors and the hot-blooded songs of the countless Latin immigrants there. Here, you're at the crime capital of New Mexico. Albuquerque is statistically less safe than Mexico City in literal Mexico.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What are you thinking thus far?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Foremost, I am thinking that it's a real blessing this Coke is still cold, came straight from the fridge. But aside from that…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Myy dream came true…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Aside from that, what?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's been pretty real so far. We got that Jane in custody and Doug is going to assume the others are working their own angles. Now would be a pretty decent time for Doug to do something for himself.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Come in contact with a friendly, possibly? Is that an option?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: What kind of friendly?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Well, that's the question, isn't it? How is the state of the investigation looking like? Leads on whatever that "Angular Atelier" was would be pertinent to pursue.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: I'm crazy for tryin'…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content:
You think about it for a while. You can't think of a reason why you would need the help of a friendly to break into some bum-ass tattoo shop and question the owner.

You're reading the national newspaper on the side. First page is reserved for the upcoming election, on the second, you read something about the recent "Bay Harbor Butcher" in Miami. Apparently a local sergeant from the metropolitan area PD is responsible for it. His obituary takes up just three lines- possibly one of the worst possible outcomes for a cop.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Listen, I'm telling you…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We just gotta get their help for distrib- selling!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The man behind you sounds pretty agitated.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That's really interesting to overhear. Hm…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Doug'd better keep listening. Intently.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Roll Alertness, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"We don't fucking need them, we just need to keep pushing the ice Mr. -!"

You didn't catch the name, it went down in pitch really hard.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ice"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Look you don't understand, this could be groundbreaking. You don't understand anything more complicated than downloading porn on your computer!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Their arguing cascades in tone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Might spill a lot more info if this keeps up.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: So loud, so agitated. Either very stupid or wanting someone to overhear. …But clearly no-one is that paranoid.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You try to eavesdrop for a few more minutes but fail to make anything deeper than that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finally, the guy explodes.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Not literally, I hope.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Look man, I'm fucking done with you!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'm so tired of all your shit, yeah, do this and that, heil fucking Hitler bro! I don't need you or your help!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Calm down Jesse-"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The young man grabs his things and prepares to leave. Eyes are on him.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The name "Jesse" pointedly noted.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: We'd better just let him leave. He's got the whole diner in an uproar. People are watching.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Don't fucking call me anymore, we're done, understand?!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The middle aged guy sits back on his couch, stumped.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Enough identifying traits for Doug to pick this guy out of a line-up or, say, a crowd, later?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Yes- picture perfect junkie build, but you might not immediately recognize him in the future.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The middle aged man leaves the bar soon after. You're alone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Not so very much alone, I hope? I mean, in the physical sense. People in the diner here still.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You're always alone, no matter where you go. Hell, you don't even believe in love anymore.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: May 05, 2008. Evening. The day before.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's the evening you were "too busy".
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You reckoned you'd actually dig into the reason why you are here, but if that truly doesn't interest you, you're free to fill up your time with something else.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I do try to dig into the reason we're here, yes.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Quite straightforward. Forensic accountance does highlight the details between the lines, sometimes with frightening accuracy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sun is setting, you're at the Simms building.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I will attempt to examine the forensic documentation records.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Accounting, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

tracked missing person, the book club president

investigated their domicile

found entire place ransacked and a book with most pages ripped out

found some pages that go against what he had learned during his cherished study of history

case ends inconclusive

started researching it in free time

DG's Carnivore-fork protocol detected his questions, silent alert is raised

he is contacted, debriefed thoroughly

several points he raises are analyzed and cross-referenced as useful deductions

messages.content: "Stuck on the slow desk duty? Got a moment?"
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: The hispanic woman looks for a moment at you, and then slides forward on her office chair.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "What do you need agent?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I need another pair of eyes, miss."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Looking to cross-reference a few facts and… the forensics archives are quite muddled."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: You immediately notice how patronizing that was.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Okay, sure. Which case?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Most of these files are need-to-know. Welcome to compartmentalized access.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can still worm your way past with a relevant skill.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I'll try to use my knowledge of bureaucracy and criminology to worm my way past this little bureaucratic obstacle.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Preferably the latter.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Criminology is higher. Blind roll, and since this is an area of your specific expertise, get 20% bonus.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content:
"Sure, you mean the Pistolas stuff that came in last week?"

The woman pulls up a few manila folders full of stamped copies of sales ledgers obtained from drug busts.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You nod and thank her and find a nice corner to go through them.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David, no need for yet another roll. Doesn't take a genius to understand what's going on here, and you can fairly make out the financial big picture of a 10-15 man sized gang of hispanics out of these.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: A lieutenant is inexplicably crossed out 1/3rd of the way in and is never accounted for again. Exactly a week later after the suspicious entry, another one. It doesn't say "dead" or "in custody", these are clearly noted for those who haven't turned in their shares yet to the gang leader.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: For the rest of the data, everything seems to be within the realm of routine.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That must surely mean he is either desperately hustling to make up for low sale volume, or acting treacherously. Either way, maybe a good pressure point- though I do not see any good connection to the asians here.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Perhaps the chinks may be to blame, too.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Or, it could mean a disappearance. Gangsters do have 99 reasons to skip town and never show up again.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In any case, that's all you're getting from this.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Wetbacks act in packs, there must be waves.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: May 06, 2008. 1300. USMS Holding Facility, Bernadillo Courthouse (basement).
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Everyone who wishes to show up to the interrogation are at the entrance of the holding facility. For David, he is remembering the events of this morning so far.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David. You got a call from Earle this morning about a positive ID. First instinct, issue arrest warrant. The courthouse opened fifteen minutes ago and you've met with the assistant DA.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're fairly sure you can build a warrant out of the M.O. you have. Two disappearances and possibly more, linked to a shady woman with cartels involved. The judge shouldn't be that hard to crack.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So, what do you have for me?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Roll Law, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

6'5. Skinny. Blonde, blue eyes. Disproportionate long arms. Wide face and clavicles.

was investigating federal criminal audit

money laundering. lots of incoming subscriptions, library unexpected, unjustified for the area.

turns out its actually large library book club

tracked missing person, the book club president

investigated their domicile

found entire place ransacked and a book with most pages ripped out

found some pages that go against what he had learned during his cherished study of history

case ends inconclusive

started researching it in free time

DG's Carnivore-fork protocol detected his questions, silent alert is raised

he is contacted, debriefed thoroughly

several points he raises are analyzed and cross-referenced as useful deductions

investigation think-tank permits transfer of federal asset to DG

instruction and briefing commences, works on minor cases

messages.content: She seems pleased and nods at your remarks.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Unless you have specific demands from the court or wish to drag the conversation on to attempt to get her number, your job here seems done for now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I do not.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: I am a married man, after all.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: The Honorable Judge goes through your paperwork and motions and nods approvingly. He signs the warrant. The whole affair takes about 3 minutes in his chambers.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can expect an immediate hearing. That is, if, your cell gets to her first. Which they do, but at this point you're in the dark.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Present time. USMS Holding center, right below the courthouse.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan. You're at awe at the bureucratic efficiency of Albuquerque. The central PD HQ is right across the courthouse, alongside the ABQ convention centre. It's all tightly packed in such a small area.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: At this time the entire cell is at the courthouse, who wishes to participate in the interrogation?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If "Good Cop, Bad Cop" was expected, Doug is game. He could be either.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content:
More than three agents at once might cause unforeseen reactions.

As you talk it out, federal marshals buzz around you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I would attend nearby to show a strong front in the absence of other volunteers.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Finnegan suggests two people, since that's the standard. He can ask the questions if nobody else has a pressing need to - McCannon?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Frank immediately declines to enter the cell, aware of his lack of subtlety with words and yet more terrified by the prospect of dealing with a young woman.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Finnegan's suggestion is taken into account. Two volunteers with people skills.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Which isn't him.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: I'd like to remind, since the interrogée is a woman, another woman in the room might be helpful.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If only that was an option. If only.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Samantha and Finnegan?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Does Samantha agree?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: In absence of agreement it's a direct order from team lead.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Doug and Finnegan unless objections are raised.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Here goes…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Very well. You can see two female marshals drag her into the corridor, handcuffs and all.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There's an unspoken assumption in the air that Finnegan should be the one asking questions. Mostly.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Unsurprisingly she looks like a nervous wreck. What now?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We've got a couple questions. It's important you answer them thoughtfully and carefully. Don't omit any detail." He starts. "First: Did you know Damien Lucas?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Ugh… I want a lawyer."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She does have previous arrests, after all.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Marshals did allow her a call.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can safely say whoever it is, the lawyer is going to show up within this half-hour.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Sure. You're not a suspect in anything, like I said earlier. Did you get to call your dad?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
She stares back at you.

Finnegan, Blind Persuasion.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd
messages.content:
Failure

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: "Yeah, whatever."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The air is frozen. Doesn't look like the cooperative type.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug is off to the side, trying on a variety of exciting tics in an attempt to project some kind of presence in the room.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: She looks at you stimming to yourself like a psycho and rolls her eyes. Feds, am I right?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan looks at Doug and makes a frustrated gesture with his hand. "Do you understand how serious this thing you're wrapped up and around actually is? People around you are dying - 'yeah, whatever', that's what you think about it?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
She is taken aback for a second.

"I don't know about no-one dying."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Look, I didn't skip my rehab sessions okay?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Nobody is saying you did. Damien, did you think we were trying to shake you or him down for some pills? Do you really think federal agents would roll up to your house five deep over smalltime shit?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I don't fucking know! Yes I know Damien, we hang out together but that asshole hasn't texted me since the club."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "That wouldn't happen to have been the club on Sunday, the 4th, Studio Overground, would it?" He's writing something down on a paper pad. Bullshit scribbles, but gives a sense of import.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Should Doug be writing this down? Scratch that, Doug is writing this down. Very visibly. So she sees it.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Ah, great minds think alike, then.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: They are BOTH writing it down.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content:
She thinks for a couple seconds, and then replies:

"Yeah, sure. Here you go, my alibi. Now where is my lawyer?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "If they're any good, they'll know how to get down here. In case you didn't put it together, Damien hasn't texted anyone since 'the club'. Hasn't talked to anyone, either. Or been seen. Period."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "What? What does that mean?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Gone. Poof. Not the first, and if we don't start getting some good details, probably not the last. Something is happening at that club."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
She digs her face inside her palms.

"Oh God…"

You can tell with ease that this is genuine confusion and distraught.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "If you know something, this is your chance to tell us. And if you do - and I find out you're hiding it from us - I'll make sure you're buried so deep in a federal pen that you'll forget what going to a club was ever like."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "No more music. No more friends. Collusion. Obstruction. Felony. That's curtains."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content:
She pulls herself up and rubs her temples once, wiping the tears off her eyes.

"Okay look, listen."

"There's this new shit out there. They're the Skypes, it's like, pills but in the Skype logo. You know that right? I swear-"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
BANG BANG BANG!

It's the door.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "OPEN UP! THE LAW IS HERE!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The same female marshals undo the external lock and let a guy inside.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well hi there! Your first arrest agent? If you don't know yet it's time you step outside and let me talk to my client ALONE."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Briefcase in one hand, yellow coffee mug in other. Bluetooth earpiece on, balding.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Come on now, shoo, shoo, you're about to violate an amendment!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You're late. What are you talking about?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
"Oh come on, just haul your butt out of here, I got five more clients after this."

Very clearly and obviously he is asking for you two to leave, and it's not exactly something you can refuse without putting your badge on the line.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We'll be outside. She's not in any trouble. Not yet."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Yeah right, and she shall NEVER BE!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Alright. We're going." What an outstandingly strange person.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "If I had a dime…" He looks at Doug and steps out. "Make sure you get this guy's card before he dips."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Defense attorneys…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I will."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You two wait outside the cell.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: About 20 minutes elapse. You two get coffee. The door unlocks and the marshals ask you to return inside.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So she knows about the pills, at least we got that." He murmurs to Doug. "But she knows something more about them. Maybe the upstream."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "You don't think we're getting anything more out of her with this guy in the room, are we?" Doug whispers back to Finnegan.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You two get back in the room.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"Please, take a seat agents."

Everyone is seated.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"Now, here's the deal. The case is dropped against my client, my client agrees to part all information she has about the subject alongside being obliged to stay in Albuquerque for the next three months."

"And- my client consents to future house searches and solicitations in case more evidence is levied against her, which she assures, will certainly not happen."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
She shuffles uncomfortably around her chair.

"Three months…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan tries to reign in genuine surprise. "It sounds like we can pick up right where we left off, then."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I need to hear the magic words 'yes we agree' come out of your mouth first, agent."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: This is, in fact, legally binding.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We'll take it."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "That sounds… very reasonable. Agreed."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: He sighs a relief and takes a sip out of the big yellow mug. You notice it says "WORLDS BEST LAWYER" on it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You were saying - the pills?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Okay, so, there's this new shit on the street and Damien has been selling it. He's a fucking asshole so I don't care if he gets arrested anymore, we were just together for the stuff."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "They are called the Skypes. I don't know what exactly it is but it's like, ecstasy on steroids."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Damien hangs out with the cholos but told me that he's been getting it from a black guy, personally."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan makes sure Doug is writing this all down. "And he never named names, did he?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "He kept calling a 'Mad Dog' on his phone but I don't know his real name. Probably Juan Ignacius or some bullshit, I really don't know."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She scratches on her arms uncomfortably.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 'Mad Dog', yeah, Doug's writing it down.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Enough about 'Skype' for now." He clears his throat. "You go to Studio Overground often?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Yeah, it's a cool place to hang out."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ever heard anything about people going missing? Think carefully."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I think I came across the cops twice there in the past month but they say there's definitely been more of them hanging around."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Didn't really care about it."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Not for nothing." He reaches for the picture of Spider. "Ever seen this guy there?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: She shuffles for a second, and then is interrupted by Saul. They whisper to eachother for a moment.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah, this is the guy who used to sell me the same stuff before Damien took over, I guess."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Happen to know his name?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: She shakes "no".
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The pill itself is really hot shit, though."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I bet you mormons have no idea, but it's partying on another level once you pop one."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Mormons..?" Doug mumbles that then clears his throat. In some manner of awkwardness.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Mormons and FBI, google it, or don't.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Or DEA, they do have a big presence in there too.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan offers a condescending smile. "The night Damien was last seen by your - at the club, you said - did anything happen to him that you remember? Someone he talked to, maybe. Or he seemed off."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "He was tweaking off his mind, must have popped at least three doses."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Definitely on the same shit. Was describing the stuff that happened to him as a toddler, it was… weird."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Have you ever seen someone get hurt from taking these pills? Like an overdose, maybe."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Actually, no. Even in my narcotics anonymous group I haven't heard of anyone getting hurt by it."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She scoffs, having to mention that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Maybe it's some new type of LSD, who knows."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So Damien is telling you some kind of childhood memories - and he goes into the bathroom."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I was in the mood to dance, I didn't really care much afterwards and got pissed when he wasn't lying next to me the next morning like how he usually ends up."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "The pill grips strong, man, it's like time stretches and you feel the same good feeling over and over again."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Feels like it's never gonna end. And then you realize you've been on the dance floor for six straight hours."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ever heard of someone smoking it? Crushed up, maybe, out of a pipe."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I think I actually holed in like that once too, I took two pills once and saw myself in the classroom getting bullied for being anorexic in middle school. It was like, everyone was right in front of me once again and their laughter just echoing, inside my ears…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Her stare drifts off into space.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hey, stop, you don't have to go there."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're clearly smarter than Doug to pick up on this. She is painting a crystal clear picture of a memory that should be repressed due to trauma.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're feeling like an underpaid therapist. SAN roll, blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It made me think hypnotic regression therapy.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: Doug is too busy taking notes. Last line so far reads "EFFECTS: AGE REGRESS?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You seem to resonate with it. Too hard.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The feeling you had in the club bathroom is coming back.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's like you're in that classroom with her, cruelly laughing at the thin brunette girl sitting a few desks behind you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your laughs erupt in a cacophony and spit is flying everywhere. Children can be so cruel, inhumane even.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The old and shrewd geography teacher interrupts the class, but all of you continue laughing, choking on your own laughter, in unison.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She's crying but you do not understand a thing about her pain. Empathy is alien to you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You snap back to your senses. Now, the same girl has grown up into a woman, looking at you once again in helplessness, like a cornered animal.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You may blind roll 1d4 to deflect some of the harsher feelings.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Or refuse, if you wish to keep it all to yourself.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Better not to talk about this kind of stuff. No roll.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Another nightmare in your collection. You may continue interrupting her, in reality.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "…Miss Margolis. The pills. Smoking. Did you ever see anyone… Smoke them." He stops. "Liao. They called it Liao. I think you heard them say it."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "It doesn't matter, it all hits about the same."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "That's a yes or no question." He glares at the lawyer.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Yes. You can crush it, smoke it, shove it up your ass, I just said the high is the same."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ever notice particular groups of people using it particular ways?" He taps his finger on the table. "Let me get down to brass tacks for you. Asians. Asians in Studio Overground."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Nah, I don't swing that way."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Never hired an escort off that club."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She raises her hands in reveal.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "No shit."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "But they're there. I've seen them. You've seen them. Do you know who they are? They're not exactly ABQ poster children."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Alright look, this has nothing to do with my client."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Doug, I need to get some water. You've got it."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "My client does not recall soliciting any sex worker for services."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Doug sighs. "I've got it."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Hey, are we done here?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Were we talking about, sex workers, just now? The question raised is still about the drug. Asians. Studio Overground? Really, never heard or seen none of it?"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "It's not her-"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Relax, I know about the asian prostitutes there. They aren't strippers or anything, it's just like, where they do their business."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's not illegal in this state, as far as I know."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "But I really have nothing to do with any of them."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Would she be correct, in this case? Doug obviously knows, but just for posterity.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: You know what? Roll Law.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Again, blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sounds convincing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Then Doug is convinced. Well, aside from that…
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: There's nothing immediately relevant that catches his attention. He's kind of at a loss.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Well, I guess our little conversation is over."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Another 'epic win' for Saul Goodman Esquire, like the kids say."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ahem. Er- sir, just one more thing."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Might I see a business card of some sort? Just to get acquainted. As we should be following this."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content:
"Sure, here ya go."

He hands you one each.

"I only practice in New Mexico, though."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It really is 'Esquire'. Well, figures.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "Unless you end up in the Land of Enchantment with no possibility of extradition to D.C. I don't see you being my client."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I'll remember that. Appreciate it."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Pff, what a relief."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"Sure."

He is packing his stuff in his briefcase.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Handshakes are exchanged and Saul takes off.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Everyone besides Doug, Finnegan and Cliff, state what you are doing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You're all within the immediate vicinity of the courthouse.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Didn't I have a meeting with a CI?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You got a few more hours to that.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's at 4PM.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon asks for Finnegan to give him the lowdown of what's up and asks if Doug was of any use in addition.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: David is smoking a cigarette.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Finnegan shakes his head. "One lead. Upstream from Lucas. Black, goes by 'Mad Dog'. Other than that, just a girl's diary about what it's like to throw back pills."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Such is life.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Thinking about the bigger picture over a coffee while he waits for Doug and Finn. What's going on here? His first thought were that the pills were enthralling people or something, but from what Finn told them yesterday it's likely that members of Tong Shukoran itself are taking the very drug being sold at that club. It's all sideways and he can only curse his lack of creativity at how stumped he is.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: David. As you are chiefing on that hoe, you notice a strange looking bench.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Anything else? You look like you've seen a ghost."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: I stroll towards the bench in a leisure manner and take a closer look- oh my, how garish.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: This would never happen in D.C.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's embarrassing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: These people really have no taste.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Nah. Nothin'."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You're all exchanging thoughts inside the holding facility, while Cliff is still working on the sample. David is smoking outside.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You sure?" He stares Finnegan directly in the eyes.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Just something in her eyes. Freaked me out. It's nothing."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Two figures are approaching you, clearly not marshals.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "…It's good she's in a program, that's all."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: David heads back inside.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Heyyy, fellas."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I heard you already got an arrest in."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Long time no see."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: This guy is staring at you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Fuckin… alternate lifestyles-" McCannon turns towards Schrader as he gets interrupted mid-sentence.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He is the same guy who was staring at you when you were at the computer lab this morning.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle stares back at him appearing vaguely confrontational, but silent.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: He puts both thumbs into his belt, displaying a rotund belly unbecoming of a federal agent.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So, what's the scoop?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Same shit eating smile from yesterday.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

Success

messages.content: Earle, there's nowhere to hide here and he just stares at you for a moment, before returning to McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Potent pressed MDMA pills on the street and two dealers of the shit in a row disappeared. We got Type O Negative #1 fan in there with a… uhhh," McCannon clicks his fingers trying to remember "Saul Goodman, I think?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
"Type O… what?"

He grins.

"She's also got Goodman for attorney?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I swear every half wit piece of shit in this town is downstream of him."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
"Maybe we oughta run him outta here sometime Gomie."

He is returned with a snarky smile.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "So she's not connected to the disappearance?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Not necessarily, but she did identify 'the Spider' as a previous dealer."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "I see."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Of the pills, I mean."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Anything else?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well, she's attending rehab, but from what I hear this isn't the usual XTC we're dealing with."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: His smile fades.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
He puts a hand on your shoulder, McCannon.

"Can we talk over there for a second?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan leaves his hands in his pockets and exhales deeply.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "What's this about?" Doug remarks to the others in a low whisper
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: McCannon has his hands on his hips looking downwards at nothing in particular.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Look, next time you write up a warrant why don't you try giving me a call alright? Especially when it's concerning a two-cent junkie slut."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We're shitting in his backyard, Doug." Finnegan says.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I know El Paso is the real elite high speed low drag shit, I've been there for a while, but here we gotta bite the big fish only, you know what I mean?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah, how we brought that junkie in? I understand McCannon is not going to hear the end of this."
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: "I was hoping we'd avoid this whole, whatever you call it… feds-versus-locals thing…"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "It'll be fine."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He's still staring at you talk to the other two, he very clearly has not seen you around before.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Yeah, I understand," McCannon replies, looking back at his team for a second, "I'm trying to reign in these chucklefucks and have us pace ourselves, but you know how agents are when there's glory involved."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He turns around to his flip phone, messaging someone.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "This chick wasn't even worth a warrant, let's be real, she's just some fucking party girl."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
"Alright, just find glory where it actually is, not in the back of some club, agent."

He pats you on the shoulder once more and turns to leave.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Let's go, it's lunch break."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Right."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: They get out fast, brushing against some marshals.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And how about the rest of the crew? Jane's hearing is in an hour, right after the lunch break.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I join the others.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: David. Your smile fades when you find out you are dropping the case.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Don't worry about it, though. Happens all the time, especially when important evidence is uncovered.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Hell was up with the Mexican? Mad dogging me…"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "Don't talk to him."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Anything but the fucking truth, or so the elders hath said.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I didn't and I won't."
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: "David, consult me before you decide to pull a warrant."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Don't patronize him for it, you didn't say no.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "They think we're going to stumble onto some sketchy shit they're into. I think that's pretty clear."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Right. You recover your sidearms and exit the holding facility.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: 1500, The hearing went without any bumps and the case is dropped. Jane left for home, now you are back out in the wide world.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Decide your actions.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: When was the CI meeting due for?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: In an hour.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon is going to prep for that.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Anything to follow up on regarding that connection with the 'Mad Dog'? …Probably not. Not even so much as a name, and there must be a hundred Mad Dog beaners in this whole damn state.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Finnegan is willing to stake out the tattoo parlor if nobody has a more pressing use for one of the vehicles. Owner might turn on.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Spot-on thinking Doug. No objection.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I assume they've shared what happened in the interrogation with everyone else?
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: McCannon, you take a cab to the location and leave the corolla for someone else.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: MISCLICK. Carry on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yes, all of you have a clear idea of what happened.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan staking out alone or anyone else want to join him?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If he does not object. After all, he and Doug make such a great team together.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Earle would love to feel useful too.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: David, Earle, decide your actions.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I join Finnegan.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Plenty of people for that Tattoo Parlor, then, and he's not needed. In that case…
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Earle had an inkling on the fourth that he might be able to modify the group's ARs with someone's help and he'll chase that lead up again, if he has the time. Perhaps a little research online and he'll find some militia nuts that are able to help him?
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Looks like M.D. Samantha Cliff is… temporarily indisposed. Can she be said to be even doing anything at all, anything that is relevant to the goings on?
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: Friendly reminder of the multitude missing persons reports you have not crossreferenced.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle. Blind Criminology at a 20% bonus.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cliff is working on the sample, it's taking a huge chunk of time.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Makes sense.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The forensic reports I just found in the archives  you mean?
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Stakeout team has the SUV and Earle has the corolla so he doesn't scream federal agent to the world.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You got wind of some crazy white dude on his ranch right next to the Petroglyph Monument handling these kinds of things.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
He can machine the auto sear and the necessary modifications to the lower receivers for an Unusual expense.

For a bargain… you did see a couple Gadsden flags on your way in. Time for a friendly chat?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Absolutely. No idea how to broach a topic like this without seeming like a cop but at least they seem to have something in common.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: It's second nature to you, just speak your mind with a blind Persuasion roll at a 20%+.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If you're lost just hit the roll.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

Slightly overweight, brown hair combed to one side, chevron moustache.

a- Born 1980 in Paris Texas to a single mother. Rough upbringing led him to (mostly) forswear drugs and alcohol, developed a complex against middle America, 'hicks' etc.

- Became interested in computer science during the dot-com bubble and left home to study I.T at 18.

- Married in 2003 while working the help-desk at Cisco. Made the majority of his income at this time via cable piracy - running services that could decrypt smart cards, set-top boxes etc.

- Became interested in libertarianism and conspiracy culture at around this time, which tied into much of his hacking work; claims to have worked with Gary McKinnon, among others.

- Joined FBI Operational Technology division in 2005, in part for work experience and in part to enter the 'belly of beast' as far as his interests are concerned ('is the government really messing with the weather?' etc).

- Continues to work in this capacity alongside his side-hustles; regarded by colleagues as reliable, if a little eccentric.

messages.content: "…I figure if I ask for anything too particular, I'll sound like the guy that done bagged Randy Weaver, so I'll let you name your price to work on these and leave it at that. Y'good to work on five?"
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: Earle. He agrees to do it for Standard expense only if you listen to his rants while sharing a bowl. Might fuck you up if you have an unscheduled drug test in the next 6 months. If you see the next 6 months.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Not too fond of drugs but he hasn't much of a choice here and they're taking greater risks anyway, so he obliges the man.
messages.author: TLoil0zu5jJvT6zd

messages.content: You toke up.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Yes, he does make you listen to hip-hop the whole time.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's been years since you smoked weed and this strain hits you like a fucking truck.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You sink into the couch and get the munchies.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's looking like you're stuck here way into the evening.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Better come up with a good explanation for what the fuck you've been out doing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Your ARs are now select-fire.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Stakeout team.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Hours are flowing by.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's just a tattoo parlor. Lowlives in, lowlives out, with new body marks.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You see a few bikers and that's about all the "gang activity" you can figure out from this distance.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You also see two trannies go in and out.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David, you're also here taking the best comforts the back seat has to offer.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The reports I mentioned, it's not clear if you can cross reference the forensic accountance stuff to filed missing persons reports, gangsters don't tend to do that
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You might get lucky.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David attempts to do the needful.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: You can not do anything here at the stakeout. You're stuck.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That could be your next action, though.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David will keep that in mind and for now, simply watch the crossdressers parade around the tattoo parlor.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Hope you enjoy the view.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan, wishing to deviate from the plan or?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Right on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Then, we are moving onto the CI meeting.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Before that, 10 minute break.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Continuing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan, make an INT roll, blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: As you see a tranny and a gay guy smooch eachother about 30 yards away, you suddenly revert to the first principle and run the investigation back through your mind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It occurs to you that you never actually bothered Googling anything about the Tchotcho, let alone seeking other forms of academic insight.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Furthermore, like many US cities, Albuquerque has it's own little chinatown also.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's more like a China "strip", small in size and adjacent to the main Central Avenue cutting the city in half.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: More interesting than a local cruising spot, that's for sure. Who's in the car?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: You three.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Let's see what's open in China"town".
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: We'll text McCannon just so he knows which way we're headed.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: I'm gathering that you're leaving these two on the stakeout and going your own way.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: If they're feeling inspired to keep watching this place for a suspicious-looking black male or anything else of interest
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Makes sense. I'd come with him to Chinatown if possible.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Doug is staking out alone. It's just a ten minute ride from where you stand so he does drive you up there first.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Easy.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Doug. Alertness, blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Stakin' out ain't easy.
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The tattoo shop is definitely a hangout spot. Not everyone walks out holding a limb in mild pain. That's about all you gather.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan and David.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You two take a stroll through the Chinatown.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: About as usual as it gets. Wet market, noodle shop, gift shop, nail salon…
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Some are closed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Any young masters we might notice as part of the local crime scene- enforcers or protection racketeers?
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Even if they were, by your gut feeling, you can tell that none of these resident chinamen would say a word about being extorted for protection money even if they were paying.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That's just how it works.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content:
There is a very genuine and rustic looking tea shop that caught your attention. It's almost like it's trying to hide away from plain view. So simple yet so unmistakably… Chinese. Everything about it.

It did occur to you that most of the people manning the wet market stalls and the sushi joints were actually speaking Vietnamese.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Anyone else and it would have flied right past their head.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: One problem though, the tea shop is closed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "OWNER SICK. RETURN TWO DAY."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Single-story building? Finnegan has been trying to summarize his Tcho-Tcho theory of Tong identity to David while they walk.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Yep. However, everything is in plain sight from where you stand. Past the barred windows the interior is full of Chinese medicinal herbs you can immediately recognize, such as lemon balm and ginseng. Dried, powdered, pulverized… if this is some money laundering front there is some genuine know how behind it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "What are these… Tcho-Tcho?"
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: To make a long story short, they're an ethnic minority in China, and he overheard an unmistakable word related to them while they were questioning the club. Moreover, it concerns him that the word and meaning is fairly old, even when "Skype pills" are self-evidently very new.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Alertness, Blind.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd
messages.content:
Success

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

6'5. Skinny. Blonde, blue eyes. Disproportionate long arms. Wide face and clavicles.

was investigating federal criminal audit

money laundering. lots of incoming subscriptions, library unexpected, unjustified for the area.

turns out its actually large library book club

tracked missing person, the book club president

investigated their domicile

found entire place ransacked and a book with most pages ripped out

found some pages that go against what he had learned during his cherished study of history

case ends inconclusive

started researching it in free time

DG's Carnivore-fork protocol detected his questions, silent alert is raised

he is contacted, debriefed thoroughly

several points he raises are analyzed and cross-referenced as useful deductions

investigation think-tank permits transfer of federal asset to DG

instruction and briefing commences, works on minor cases

messages.content: As you are flipping the pages, David abruptly stops you to point you at a certain "protection ward" that you made a note of in plain English.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The same kind that the superstitious love to draw on everything. This stuff transcends culture and brings oldheads of the world together.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It does heavily resemble a Chinese character but to the trained eye is "off" in every way.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Good eye. Call the boss, this isn't coincidence."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: I want to see around the sides and back of the building: Windows, doors?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: I give the boss a call on my phone.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: The back alley is easily accessible. From the dimensions of the building you can tell the upper residential floor is completely seperate from the storefront, and that there's just a small backroom with a window peering inside.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The upper floor is accessed through the entrance and the staircase adjacent to the main building, serving no other purpose. Could be illegal building code, you're totally unsure.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That's fucked up. "The owner is up there, if he's really sick at all. Someone involved is. We need them."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Roll Alertness.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Public.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.
