messages.content: You hear heavy coughing from an old man from the residential floor.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: And the voice of a young girl comforting him.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We might be able to talk our way inside. I'm not sure." He wipes the rapidly-forming sweat from his forehead. "How long until someone else gets here?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Did my call get picked up?
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Finnegan. This very clearly does not look like a drug gang clandestine base of operations.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: No fancy cars around, no suspicious figures, just some Chinese people walking around, one pushing a stroller.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It doesn't, but the odds of someone from an incredibly obscure ethnic group involved in this whole thing in New Mexico not being somehow involved seem astronomically slim.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: However the owner might be true to blood Tchotcho from what you've just seen.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Well, Finnegan, did you actually check in with an immigration authority?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Shooting from the hip aren't we.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David, your call is declined.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Boss is busy.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We could always ask ICE how many visas are issued to self-identified Tcho-Tchos with legal residence in NM, but that could be a crapshoot. These people might just mark themselves as Han.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Can see that working. Will you peer inside the window, though? You can get to it if you stand on some crate.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Absolutely.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: No need to roll Alertness again. Just the sleepy backroom of a tea shop. One small round table, few chairs, some caligraphy art on the walls.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: One scroll is covered over with a beautiful piece of rug.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Finnegan, we may be able to trick him into giving up intel, considering he might be feverish and not fully alert."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "There's a younger female in there with him. Probably a niece or some other relative. Might be a juvenile."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "That's if he even can understand us- but with a shop this nice, he's either funded by some stronger party or he actually gets some sizeable traffic. Could it be wholly chinese custom- I doubt it."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: I gotta point out your spotty reasoning, this is like saying any old Mexican is an expert at Cartel business.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Ah yes, possibly. An additional weight on his consciousness if anything untoward were to happen, even if nothing is stated or even threatened."
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Finnegan is operating under the impression that the immigrant community of a very small and obscure ethnic group in the American southwest is probably so small that any single adult member would at least know something of value.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Shall we go in?"
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: The doorbell is right there.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: There isn't any reason to believe there's a four-digit value or more of Tcho-Tchos in New Mexico or even the country, it'd be like running into Hmong in Montana.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: He rings it.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: A Chinese girl about 17 answers the door.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Good afternoon.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "What?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: White boy speaks PERFECT Mandarin.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: We used to come here on trips and saw the sign saying the owner was sick. We were hoping to see him, or ask if there was anything he needed.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Vasmin looks mildly shocked by the jade princesses' beauty, but quickly reins it in with his nordic composure.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: It's a conference a few times a year.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "He's really sick, I'm sorry but he can't see you. We don't need help, thanks."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That was in English.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan nods. "It's not flu season. Do you know what it is?"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "Pancreatic cancer. He lived with it for years and it ebbs and flows."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "He says herbs fix him more than keemotherapy, I believe him."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "We didn't know. God. That's awful."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "He says he'll be better in two more moons. Old people…"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Are you his niece, granddaughter, something? I've never seen you here."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: "I'm his granddaughter. Yi Leng."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Well, you can let him know Mike and John stopped by from Rapid City. We'll be back when it's open." He tosses his head to the side, urging David and him away.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: I head off with Finnegan.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: "Okay. Bye Mike… and John."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: She returns inside like a scared rabbit.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I want to know who this business is registered to. Property, leased or owned. I don't like it."
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content:
Vasmin nods, "Let me get the address proper…"

Vasmin notes down the address.
messages.author: MAP32PFk8MwpNfoO

messages.content: Nothing more captures your interest here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Sure thing.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: May 06, 2008. 1600. "Golden Griddle" Diner.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon. You may act.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Nothing out of the ordinary in the parking lot. The guy will meet you inside, after all.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The entrance is right there.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Affirmative.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: As soon as you step in, the overwhelming fried food smell assaults your nostrils. You're not that hungry so it's kinda gross, but no one here seems bothered.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The ambience is… old timer shit. Albuquerque feels like it's been frozen in ice since 1920s.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The state of New Mexico really has nothing going for it, doesn't it?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: What's the description of our CI?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: The guy at the cash register looks at you for a second and then returns to it.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He's wearing a hoodie and a bit chubby. Looks like a junkie.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: That guy is overweight with a tank top.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Face smudged in a burger.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Fatass.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He looks at you and doesn't break eye contact.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon takes a seat at the booth, quietly whistling some fucking tune or another.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: McCannon stops whistling and leans in, staring into the guy's eyes as he clasps his hands in front of him.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Hope no one followed you here."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon tilts his head a little, smirking, looking quietly, letting the uncomfortable silence seep in.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "So, what do you wanna know?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon lets his hands free and leans back into the cushions of the booth. "Now why would I be followed?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
"Jesus christ man, enough with the spy shit, let's just talk already."

He is undercover, not a CI, treat him like one.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon massages his brow with eyes closed, "Sure, whatever, it's your head man."
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "I'm meeting him this Friday."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Did McCannon get anything about Tcho-Tcho's mentioned to him, and in addition: does he know anything about this ethnic minority  in the first place?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: You didn't pay attention to anything past their existence. For all intents and purposes it's nerd shit to you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Does McCannon know who this schmuck is referring to in regards to a meeting?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
No. This guy most likely knows you as "his new case officer."

Fuck. McCannon! You just realized you need to adlib this whole thing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The usual, of course.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Jesus, man, I got a gajillion POIs I need to keep track of. Which one?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
"The motel. The one down by…"

He gives you an address. I'm too lazy to crossreference it on Google Earth, but it's clear where it is.

"It's super super down low, though. He knows he's got some heat on him now, after the kid disappeared."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon can hazard a guess that it's the black dude. "What was that fuckin' guy's nickname again?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Lucas. Fucker gets whole three bags of the shit and then skips town. Can you believe it?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Wait, he's back?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "No, man, no. Pastor gave him all that shit to go sell it and now he's nowhere to be found."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I think that pushed Pastor over the edge, fucker's going crazy over it. All that, combined with the PTSD, ticking time bomb."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Over some fucking Skypes?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "How would you feel if I took your 30 thousand dollars and fucked off the face of Earth?"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Guy's already mentally half gone, fucker once snuck on me like I was a god damn jihadi when I went to visit him."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "30 thousand dollars is the cost of doing business in that trade, if you can't handle that then don't do crime, I guess?" McCannon shrugs.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Naaah, it's gotta be something else…" McCannon looks out the window feigning wistfulness,
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "He's got people to answer to too, what if one of the made ones decide to show up with a chainsaw one night? It's gang shit, man."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "It's gotta be something else. What's your take on it?" McCannon turns to the guy.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He takes a sip of his coffee.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Didn't Damien Lucas get his shit from a guy named Mad Dog?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "My take is that getting constantly robbed like that, combined with a few tour of duties, I hope guy won't just brain himself before we arrest him."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Jane never implied that Mad Dog actually supplied Lucas, only that they are acquinted.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "You know anyone with the nickname Mad Dog?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Blind Persuasion.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

messages.content: "You sure you not mixing up cases? Probably some spic out there."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Little birdie told me that Lucas was banging some dude's phone with that name. It probably is some spic, but….." McCannon looks out the window again for a second then shakes his head: "Naah…"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Well, I gotta go actually, let little birdie know that no one goes near the motel until ASAC signs on it. Bring SWAT when he does."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "I swear there are hidden cameras and shit around that place. Guy is fucking psycho from all the hajjis."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Little birdie is not as import as you think it is," McCannon nods, "Fucking GWOT, am I right?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: He smirks.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Thanks for the coffee."
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He leaves, quick.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon leans on the table, unsatisfied.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Pastor is the black dude who supplied Lucas, probably reports to some higher up people,  GWOT veteran, hallmarks of PTSD from the description.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Mad Dog might be a Studio Overground connect.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: No government name, but with the address and the way he described the spot you may definitely bark up something.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Or maybe he's totally wrong, he's just a doppleganger for some fucking case officer.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Diaz wouldn't do this to you, you hope.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon ponders on if he should run after that fucker and blow his head off before he gets impatient and calls in Schrader himself.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Before you hit the speed dial.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Much like all undercover ops this one is compartmentalized and one you are not supposed to know about.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You can stir BIG shit if you do this.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Probably DEA cell moves involved here, house of cards shit.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Why didn't they just send in a DEA embedded cell in the first place? More questions, no answers, little time.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Many answers, actually, none that you can know and still keep living.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Earle is occupied. Cliff is done with the lab and in the quantum foam. Doug still on the stakeout.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: David will dig up records regarding the tea shop.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He is back at the courthouse for it, no big deal.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon, Finnegan, you feel like you could squeeze one more thing out of today.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I got nothing; just thinking about what it all means.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Still aversive to computers I see.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Go to Google.com and ask it to give you INFORMATION on TCHO TCHO's Finnegan
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "TCHOTCHO CAMBODIA CHINA PEOPLE DISPLACED"
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Not sure, could probably do a quick check on the motel. Did the car have any binos?
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: No binos. But you can do a quick driveby of it, and get away doing so.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Spin the blockaroo, then.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: Blind Alertness with a 20%-
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr
leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

Brown hair and small, baby blue eyes, of average height and build.

UB B.A. Criminal Justice

Born a military brat to officer father in Fort Meade, a life in the service of the government of the United States of America was certainly not unexpected, if a little typical of people of similar backgrounds.

Joining Baltimore PD in 1995, and graduating with a B.S. in Criminal Justice from the University of Baltimore in 1999 Michael, feeling constrained by the limitations of service to his nation in Baltimore, joined the FBI that same year, undergoing his 20 weeks at the FBI Academy in Quantico and quickly joining it's Criminal Investigative Division.

Post 9/11 Michael volunteered to transfer to FBI's Counterterrorism Division and spent the better part of the early 2000s helping hunt America's enemies within and without, transferring back to the CID in late 2006.

RED-FACED NEW ENGLAND G-MAN. A LIFETIME OF BUZZED HAIR. METICULOUSLY CLEAN-SHAVEN. HEAVY GLASSES.

RICHARD JOHN FINNEGAN. His pastor says the

middle name refers to the apostle; his parents picked it

to honor the late, great Irish Catholic president of the

United States. A third-generation New Jersey badge-

wearer.

A serious, driven asset to national security routinely

grappling with his unfortunate;y \"weak stomach\".

Growing up, he had the flu every winter - on assignment

to Washington, allergies kept him nearly bedridden. A

consummate \"clean freak\" at home and at work.

At Rutgers, he was able to turn a orientalist interest in

Chinese literature into a valuable professional skill: After

being offered a position in the FBI, he's been perpetually

on call to the west coast, to Manhattan and other

hotbeds of Mandarin-speaking crime, foreign and

domestic.

An active Chinese fiction discussion forum poster.

messages.content: Effortlessly, you find something interesting indeed.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You don't have access to the whole paper, but you can read the abstract for free.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I make note of the DOI in case we need to pull the full thing later, that should just be a call away.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Do you one better, you could probably fly to Chicago and talk to the professor yourself. That is, if you have a question that is not answered on this paper.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's from 10 years ago, Henrietta Cole is a PHD in Anthropology now.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan thinks the idea of such a people existing as described is disturbing, to say the least.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: UNM is five minutes away too. But you don't know about the Humanities there.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: State of the art hospital, however.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Is there any census-derived data I can find online that points to a lot of these people (or not) living in the US, and particularly in NM?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: No. Such research is pretty frowned upon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Racially profiling regions.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's something the census does track, since it affects districting in some cases, but maybe the group is just too small to be it's own self-reported category.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: The NGO published stuff claims the national Tchotcho population doesn't exceed 50 thousand.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Any Chinese-language sources, before we close out?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: The book you researched has more info on the ethnic group than the stuff they pumped out.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Strangely- no. No traces of the Tcho Tcho exists on the Chinese side of the internet.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Chalk it up to controlled information.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Thank you Party.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Right. Time flows on.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: It's 9PM.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Everyone is ready to move, though, unless you want to suffer insomnia the move is to sleep.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Let me clear what David found first, the store is registered to the granddaughter and seems legit on all accounts. Dates back to 1970s.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Cliff has been driving back and forth SECOM and PDHQ to crossreference missing person reports with similar circumstances. You turn up 3 more. Victims- all past drug charges.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Pretty safe to say that your serial killer slash abducter does have a M.O. concerning drug users only. If, he exists.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: What's the move?
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Finnegan wants to go back to the store, he's stuck on it. If anyone has a better idea, speak up.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: And this time, we're not knocking.
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: Finnegan. The place is just like you left during afternoon and lights are on around you.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: The chances of you two sneaking inside without being detected is nearly zero- all entrances are barred and getting past requires power tools or very solid lockpicking, both of which you do not have.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Don't we have a halligan in the car?
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: If the girl has a gun (probably does considering she owns the place) and peeked out to finish you it would be fully in self defense.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Halligan won't help you with bars, only with steel doors. There are bars over doors, detroit gas station style.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: Oh, exterior security doors
messages.author: PgyzRoJpXTIEjkpd

messages.content: So we're assuming two bedrooms, one juvenile female, one adult male, separate - or maybe not, considering these people. Anyone have a useful tool or idea? I doubt they're going to open the door again.

messages.content: All things put together it's starting to become clear you are wasting time here.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: I have no ideas aside from the code uncompliant door.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: We are probably going to have to talk to them again during daylight hours.

messages.content: Serves us right for scoping out Chinese Fort Knox.

messages.content: The situation with the door is fucked Chinesium architecture, yes

messages.content: You just love a 40 minute drive on no traffic, don't you.

messages.content: Probably mention the fact that the undercover guy is meeting with a crazed GWOT veteran who may or may not be getting drugs from a specific ethnic minority (the name of which is delivered in anagram form.)

messages.content: "pmc or marine?"

"dod money is no joke i guess."

She disconnects.

messages.content: McCannon.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: You wake up to your burner ringing.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: McCannon sits up in bed and picks up the phone.
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content:
It's Schrader.

"Heyy, Agent. I think I got your 'missing person' here. You gotta come see this. We're at…"

He describes the address of a multi-story car park.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Huh?"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "Looks like the cholos got to him first, too bad!"
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: He hangs up.
messages.author: 4CGWQNBhrWtE51Tr

messages.content: "Motherfucker!" McCannon tosses the burner aside and gets dressed as if he has to toss on CBRN gear during a gas attack. Once he's dressed he starts banging the doors of his fellow agents "WE'RE MOVING! GET DRESSED!"
messages.author: leqfJ3KIQNqNXMV8

messages.content: "What the-- Yeah, coming!"
messages.author: rGQWFMrwXQMDudzI

messages.content: The drive takes you 50 minutes and you're practically out-raced by everyone else to the scene.

messages.content: Indecipherable grumbling as he puts his britches on and gets rerady.
